      "text": "@SecWar Hegseth delivered powerful remarks this morning to military leaders from 34 countries to open the first ever Western Hemisphere Chiefs of Defense Conference hosted by the Chairman of the Joint Chiefs Gen. Dan Caine and the Joint Staff. \n\nSome excerpts: \n\n“Under President Trump, for the first time in history, the Department of War is on offense against narco-terrorists in our hemisphere.” \n\n“Through President Trump’s leadership and tenacity - his unwillingness to accept the status quo - we are protecting our shared interests in our shared hemisphere.” \n\n“And we must do this together.” \n\n“We must work together to prevent any adversary or criminal actor from exploiting your territory or using your infrastructure to threaten what a great former American president, Teddy Roosevelt, once called “permanent peace in this hemisphere.” \n\nTo put America First, we must put the Americas First. President Trump’s National Security Strategy and National Defense Strategy has done this. It’s time to get to work.",
      "text_resolved": "@SecWar Hegseth delivered powerful remarks this morning to military leaders from 34 countries to open the first ever Western Hemisphere Chiefs of Defense Conference hosted by the Chairman of the Joint Chiefs Gen. Dan Caine and the Joint Staff. \n\nSome excerpts: \n\n“Under President Trump, for the first time in history, the Department of War is on offense against narco-terrorists in our hemisphere.” \n\n“Through President Trump’s leadership and tenacity - his unwillingness to accept the status quo - we are protecting our shared interests in our shared hemisphere.” \n\n“And we must do this together.” \n\n“We must work together to prevent any adversary or criminal actor from exploiting your territory or using your infrastructure to threaten what a great former American president, Teddy Roosevelt, once called “permanent peace in this hemisphere.” \n\nTo put America First, we must put the Americas First. President Trump’s National Security Strategy and National Defense Strategy has done this. It’s time to get to work.",
